those, 88,8% had abnormalities, being the most frequent ventricular 
repolarization changes.There was not influence of the parameters on the 
frequency of abnormal ECG. The abnormalitees of the ECG, especially those 
secondary to ischemia were related with intraoperative complications in all 
study groups.
CONCLUSIONS: This study has shown that electrocardiogram is a valid routine for 
preoperative evaluation of elderly patients.

