sociodemographic parameters were, in most cases, small. The preferences obtained 
with the SF-6D could discriminate patients with different HAQ levels.
CONCLUSION: The SF-6D is a valid method for measuring preferences in patients 
with rheumatoid arthritis in a Brazilian context.

