restrictive lung disease (10.42% and 0.03%). Incidences were significantly 
higher in group 1. Additionally, the following problems were found in group 1, 
but not in group 2: epilepsy (2.08%), nonalcoholic fatty liver (12.5%), gall 
bladder stones (6.25%), dyslipemia (20.83%) and hypopytuitarism (2.08%).
CONCLUSIONS: The prevalence of clinical problems was significantly higher in 
morbidly obese patients as compared to their non-obese counterparts.

